**Custom Font 1: Implementation and Usage**
=====================================================

In this example, we will implement a custom font, `font1.ttf`, in a web application using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. We will also explore how to integrate this font with a PHP-based backend and a MySQL/MariaDB database.

**Frontend Implementation**
-------------------------

### HTML

To use the custom font in our HTML, we need to include a link to the font file in the `<head>` section of our HTML document.

```html
<head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
```

### CSS

In our CSS file, `styles.css`, we will define the `@font-face` rule to import the custom font.

```css
@font-face {
    font-family: 'Custom Font 1';
    src: url('fonts/font1.ttf') format('truetype');
}

.custom-font {
    font-family: 'Custom Font 1', sans-serif;
}
```

### JavaScript

We can use JavaScript to dynamically apply the custom font to elements on our webpage.

```javascript
// Get all elements with the class 'custom-font'
const customFontElements = document.getElementsByClassName('custom-font');

// Apply the custom font to each element
for (const element of customFontElements) {
    element.style.fontFamily = 'Custom Font 1, sans-serif';
}
```

**Backend Implementation (PHP)**
------------------------------

To integrate the custom font with our PHP-based backend, we can use PHP to generate CSS stylesheets or to serve the font file directly.

### Serving the Font File

We can use PHP to serve the font file directly by creating a script that reads the font file and outputs its contents with the correct MIME type.

```php
// font.php
header('Content-Type: font/ttf');
readfile('fonts/font1.ttf');
```

### Generating CSS Stylesheets

We can use PHP to generate CSS stylesheets that include the `@font-face` rule for our custom font.

```php
// styles.php
$fontFamily = 'Custom Font 1';
$fontSrc = 'fonts/font1.ttf';

echo <<<CSS
@font-face {
    font-family: '$fontFamily';
    src: url('$fontSrc') format('truetype');
}

.custom-font {
    font-family: '$fontFamily', sans-serif;
}
CSS;
```

**Database Integration (MySQL/MariaDB)**
--------------------------------------

To store information about our custom font in a MySQL/MariaDB database, we can create a table to store font metadata.

```sql
CREATE TABLE fonts (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
    font_family VARCHAR(255),
    font_src VARCHAR(255)
);

INSERT INTO fonts (font_family, font_src) VALUES ('Custom Font 1', 'fonts/font1.ttf');
```

We can then use PHP to retrieve the font metadata from the database and generate the CSS stylesheet or serve the font file.

```php
// db.php
$conn = new mysqli('localhost', 'username', 'password', 'database');

if ($conn->connect_error) {
    die("Connection failed: " . $conn->connect_error);
}

$sql = "SELECT font_family, font_src FROM fonts WHERE font_family = 'Custom Font 1'";
$result = $conn->query($sql);

if ($result->num_rows > 0) {
    while($row = $result->fetch_assoc()) {
        $fontFamily = $row['font_family'];
        $fontSrc = $row['font_src'];

        // Generate CSS stylesheet or serve font file
    }
} else {
    echo "0 results";
}

$conn->close();
```

**Full Example**
----------------

Here is the full example code that demonstrates how to implement a custom font in a web application using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, PHP, and MySQL/MariaDB.

### HTML

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <h1 class="custom-font">Custom Font 1</h1>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

### CSS (styles.css)

```css
@font-face {
    font-family: 'Custom Font 1';
    src: url('fonts/font1.ttf') format('truetype');
}

.custom-font {
    font-family: 'Custom Font 1', sans-serif;
}
```

### JavaScript (script.js)

```javascript
// Get all elements with the class 'custom-font'
const customFontElements = document.getElementsByClassName('custom-font');

// Apply the custom font to each element
for (const element of customFontElements) {
    element.style.fontFamily = 'Custom Font 1, sans-serif';
}
```

### PHP (font.php)

```php
